\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs22 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 1\~}
Y\u233?n\u233? Melkisedek t\u233?morw\u233?n warsagh \u225?r Salem ndimbal tesenm\u233?n a w\u233?i t\u233?morw\u233?n Minde Tuk\u233?n Ng\u225?nj\u225?nene gh\u233?ng\u233?n w\u225?rogh \u225?r. Njam Ebraam k\u233?nangotau m\u233?ngotuot soram\u233? ndimbal m\u233?kta njam nawaindai \u225?sm\u233?ghan \u225?mb t\u225?rf\u225?r warsagh \u225?rfe ngita, Melkisedek\u233?m y\u233?f\u225?ngoi f\u225? a y\u233?frendai. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 2\~}
F\u233?yo Ebraam\u233?m en\u233?rsam \u225?mbiro 10m\u233?n m\u233?inyotio y\u233?mon \u225?rk\u233? ewanai \u225?sm\u233?ghan a eramai Melkisedeke, y\u225?ne y\u233?tkw\u233?n fifi siy\u233?m, 'Warsagh \u225?r mbark\u225?ndm\u233?n.' A f\u225? t\u233?morw\u233?n Salemm\u233?n warsagh \u225?r, y\u225?ne fifi siy\u233?m, "Warsagh \u225?r krufr\u225?tm\u233?n." {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 3\~}
\u193?mb yau y\u233?kai y\u225?ne y\u225?refanem\u233?n o y\u225?tmanem\u233?n, o \u225?mb y\u225?ne y\u225?kifenem\u233?n; yau y\u233?kai y\u225?ne \u225?r\u225?f\u233?ghm\u233?n a k\u233?rm\u233?n. F\u225? m\u233? y\u233?m gh\u233?ng\u233?n w\u225?rogh \u225?r tuot, ndenanit y\u233?m Ng\u225?nj\u225?nene Ambum.
\par\pard\plain \s60\ql\fi180\lin0\rin0\sb0\sa0\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\nosupersub\cf2\fs22 {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 4\~}
Mato t\u233?fandangi nder\u233? ndimbal y\u233?n\u233? Melkisedek t\u233?morw\u233?n. Ndemam\u233?n Ebraam, Israil \u225?rfene ndimbal s\u233?nko \u225?r, mat n\u225?y\u225?toi nder\u233? ndimbal Melkisedek t\u233?morw\u233?n y\u233?nayan siyaramai y\u225? \u225?mbiro 10m\u233?n n\u233?m\u233? y\u233?mo t\u233? enmanai \u225?sm\u233?ghan. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 5\~}
S\u233?nonjo gh\u233?ng\u233?n w\u225?rogh \u225?r, efe em Lefiene \u225?ki ambum, ew\u225?f\u225?rete Mosesene n\u225?kam m\u233?n\u225?t s\u225?i ekafetat \u225?mbiro 10m\u233?n mani k\u233?tam\u233? m\u233?inyotio \u225?r tamb\u233?n, ndemam\u233?n f\u225? w\u233?i em Ebraamene \u225?kiambum. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 6\~}
W\u233?nde Melkisedek, efe yau t\u233?morw\u233?n Lefiene \u225?kim\u233?n, enkafai \u225?mbiro 1om\u233?n k\u233?tam\u233? Ebraameta a Melkisedek\u233?m yafayoi freng\u233?gh y\u225?yot Ebraame, f\u225? emo t\u233? ewanai uny\u233?ghofnar si Ng\u225?nj\u225?nenem\u233?n. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 7\~}
A amogh siofnar, \u225?r endefaf y\u233?m waft\u233? m\u233?n\u225?t freng\u233?gh\u233?t siy\u233?m t\u250?m\u233?n ndimbal y\u233?m y\u225?yot efe y\u233?frende. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 8\~}
Gh\u233?ng\u233?n w\u225?rogh \u225?r emo ekafete \u225?mbiro 10m\u233?n em \u225?r efe k\u233?r so em, w\u233?nde Melkisedek\u233?m ewainde f\u225?, m\u233?nam\u233?n t\u233?fe t\u233? y\u233?nmaufroy\u233?nd nden\u233? f\u225? gh\u233?rs\u233? m\u233? so y\u233?ng\u233?m. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 9\~}
\u193?mbiro m\u233?t\u233? korayang\u233? nden\u233? Lefi, emo ekafete \u225?mbiro 10m\u233?n, fai tawafrotau \u225?mbiro 10m\u233?n Ebraame k\u233?nj\u250?m\u233?. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 10\~}
M\u233?nam\u233?n njam Melkisedek\u233?m y\u233?f\u225?ngoi Ebraam, Lefi t\u225?f m\u233? t\u233?morw\u233?n \u225?r\u225?f\u233?ghofnar y\u225?ki k\u233?nj\u250?n.
